10 January 2020 President Cyril Ramaphosa has declared a Special Official Funeral Category 2 for esteemed business leader Dr Richard Maponya who will be buried on Tuesday, 14 January 2020 in Johannesburg, Gauteng. Dr Maponya, widely respected as the doyen of black business, passed away on Monday 6 January 2020, a few days after celebrating his 99th birthday. The President has directed that the National Flag fly at half-mast from Friday 10 January 2020 until the evening of the burial. Members of the media are invited to apply for accreditation by filling in their personal details on the attached form and sending it to Ishmael Selemale on ishmael@gcis.gov.za  or Ignicious Masilela on ignicious@gcis.gov.za. The deadline for applications is Monday, 13 January 2020 at 10h00. Details for collection of accreditation cards will be communicated as soon as possible.